---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PythagorasExplorer from '../../../components/diagrams/PythagorasExplorer.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Pythagorean Theorem" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-8/" backLabel="← Grade 8">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Pythagorean Theorem</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Discover the most famous theorem in geometry</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>a² + b² = c²</h2>
		<p>In every right-angled triangle: the sum of the squares on the two shorter sides (legs) equals the square on the longest side (hypotenuse).</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Experience Pythagoras</h3>
		<p>Change legs a and b. Watch how c follows — and how the area equation holds!</p>
	</section>

	<PythagorasExplorer client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Applications</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Calculate distance:</strong> d = √((x₂−x₁)² + (y₂−y₁)²)</li>
			<li><strong>Check if right-angled:</strong> If 3² + 4² = 5² → right angle!</li>
			<li><strong>Pythagorean triples:</strong> (3,4,5), (5,12,13), (8,15,17)...</li>
		</ul>
		<p>This only works for RIGHT triangles. The hypotenuse is ALWAYS the longest side!</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
